parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The illumination of the air bag warning light can indicate a malfunction in the air bag system, which can lead to the failure of the air bags to deploy in the event of a crash, potentially resulting in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The air bag warning light is illuminated on the instrument panel
and the air bags may not deploy in the event of a crash.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the air bags to deploy in the event of a crash can result in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The air bags do not deploy in the event of a crash
and the vehicle occupants may suffer injuries or fatalities.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the air bag system can lead to the failure of the air bags to deploy in the event of a crash, potentially resulting in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The air bag system malfunctions
and the air bags may not deploy in the event of a crash.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front control arm can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle may pull to one side
the front wheel may stick out sideways
the vehicle may collapse to the ground
or the driver may hear a loud noise.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear control arm can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle may fish tail
the rear crossmember may fall out
or the driver may hear a loud screeching noise.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Corrosion of Subframe and Control Arms
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion of the subframe and control arms can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle may exhibit excessive corrosion
the subframe may fracture
or the control arms may break away from the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brakes can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The brake pedal may feel soft or spongy
the brakes may fail to function properly
or the driver may have to apply force to the brake pedal multiple times to stop the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The illumination of the air bag indicator can cause the driver to be distracted, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The air bag indicator light may illuminate without warning
the vehicle may make a rumbling noise
or the vehicle may jerk to one side.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front control arm can cause loss of steering, leading to accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle's steering wheel vibrates or shakes
the vehicle pulls to one side
and the front tires may wear unevenly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause loss of steering, leading to accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The steering wheel is difficult to turn
the vehicle's steering wheel vibrates or shakes
and the power steering pump may leak or fail.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brakes may lock up or fail to engage
and the vehicle may vibrate or shake when braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The vibration of the steering wheel can cause loss of control, leading to accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The steering wheel vibrates or shakes
especially at high speeds
and the vehicle may pull to one side.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission and clutch can cause loss of control, leading to accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The transmission may jerk or hesitate
the clutch pedal may feel soft or spongy
and the vehicle may vibrate or shake.
